She felt the dart sink into her metal skin.  She growled at Attilla, 
reaching for her sidearm.  She pulled it out and aimed at him. Before 
she could pull the trigger, her optics blinked and then faded into 
sleep mode. She fell to the ground, out cold. Her weapon still in her 
hand.
